def make_numerical(df, cols):
    new_df = df.copy()
    for col in cols:
        new_df[col] = new_df[col].astype('category')
        new_df[col] = new_df[col].cat.codes
    return new_df

Plotting PCA result¶

In [25]:
from sklearn.decomposition import *
from sklearn.preprocessing import *
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def show_scatter_PCA(data,col_color):
    scaled_data = StandardScaler(with_mean=True,with_std=True).fit_transform(data.drop(col_color,1))
    pca1 = PCA(n_components=4)
    pca_data = pca1.fit_transform(scaled_data)
    plt.figure(get_plot())
    plt.scatter(pca_data[:,0], pca_data[:,1], c=data[col_color], alpha=0.5)
    plt.title('PCA penguins with color='+col_color)
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('y')
    plt.show()
In [30]:
for col in ['sex','island','species']:
    show_scatter_PCA(num_data.drop(['year'],1),col)
